[The number of cases of hemolytic uremic syndrome associated with this enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ outbreak is now 5 out of a total of 16, an attack rate of 31 per cent. This is substantially higher than the most standard 5-10 per cent although the numbers are, at this point, small. We await more information regarding the outbreak strain and its toxin production. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4887992,106.]
